      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 20 min, remove the lid from the paella and add the juice<strong> </strong>of 1/2<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to medium-low for the final 10 min (this will help with caramelisation) – this is your <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>chicken & chorizo paella</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> from the oven and crowd them together on one side of the baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Dollop the <strong>remaining tomato frito</strong> over the top with the <strong>remaining smoked paprika </strong>and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>– these are your <strong>patatas bravas</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>smoky chicken strips </strong>to the other side of the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for a final 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
